erofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Getting up from the table, Jzonn moves to intercept the tray with coffee, milk, and sugar.  &quot;Thanks much.  I'll take that over here, since I've been invited to join them.  I would appreciate your bringing my breakfast to that table instead.&quot;  Setting the tray on a nearby table, he quickly adds sugar and milk to the mug and stirs the liquid with the provided spoon until it turns a uniform light brown.  The spoon is placed back on the tray.<br>
<br>
A sip is carefully taken and savored.  Over the cup, Jzonn offers a smile to Casidy.  &quot;Good morning ladies&quot;, Jzonn offers before taking a seat at the table.  &quot;How are you this fine morn?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A> at: 3/6/01 9:17:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/6/01 9:46:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Febreeza?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Good morrow sir.  Hail and well met.  I am Febreeza Tinytank, Warrioress of the 45th level.  And this is my very dear friend Liandriana Sedai, Conjurer of the 55th circle.  <br>
<br>
Casidy was just going to share with us the reason for her need of counsel and assistance.  Please join us while we break the fast and see if we can't help Casidy with her task. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uliandriana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liandriana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/7/01 1:10:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lumthemad.net/hedron.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Liandriana blinked, all of a sudden there were all these impatient people trying to look patient staring at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, can you join us Liandriana?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ummm.... huh?&quot; replied Liandriana.<br>
<br>
&quot;Can you come and help us?&quot; they almost spoke in unison.<br>
<br>
&quot;I... I have things to atend to.  Perhaps at a later time i could meet up with you?&quot; <p><i><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=24077">Syui Chan</a></i> -55 Master<i><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=17311">Liandriana Sedai</a></i> -55 Conjurer <br>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/9/01 3:36:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Stared at her friend Liandriana blankly.  Wondering if she was going to be alright.  Then she remembered dealing with the Freeport Militia would often throw her friend out of kilter for a while.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's okay&quot;; she told Liandriana.  &quot;I am sure you will catch up to us later if you can.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once again Febreeza looked to the young Bard Casidy and the Ranger Jzonn.  <br>
<br>
&quot;So where were we?  Ahh... I remember... Casidy was about to tell us what the task is that she needs help with.  Pray continue, my dear&quot; she says as she beams a smile at Casidy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/9/01 5:02:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> *wrapping her arms around her for warmth as the thoughts that filled her mind brought a chill to her bones*<br>
<br>
"Well dear, I have been tasked with carrying a message to the King of Thurgadain" Casidy lowered her voice and leaned in a bit. "I am not privy to its content, but it holds critical import to those that request it of me, and to those that must receive its message."<br>
<br>
Sighing softly.<br>
<br>
"I have been given a map to guide me, but well, to be honest" Casidy paused briefly "I am one of the worlds worst at navigation, I can reach my destination but normally not by the quickest means"<br>
<br>
Seeing the odd sense of puzzlement cross the faces of the two before her.<br>
<br>
Casidy lifted her glass to sip her milk, and added softly, "One small caveat was added to the mission, I was not to entrust my passage to a druid or wizard. I can guess at the intent of this, but I can not hope to assume."<br>
<br>
Thinking on this for a moment, it was not the first time the Antonican bards had requested Casidy to maintain the decorum of a bard, and not travel under the magics of a wizard or druid from land to land. A request she had no problem with, give her a drum and the time and she was ready with a song to speed the pace.<br>
<br>
This was an unusual request in this specific case, as they had stressed the time urgency. The message was needed within two weeks time. <br>
<br>
Looking from Febreeza to Jzonn, she wondered if these two would be able to help her locate this Thurgadain city, and help her seek audience with this king.<br>
<br>
"What say you?" Casidy questioned softly, "Are you up in speeding a traveling bard on a long voyage to her specific destination?"<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">
