<br>
~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uqwiktaveren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwik Ta veren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/9/01 10:55:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> &quot;What say you?&quot; Casidy questioned softly, &quot;Are you up in speeding a traveling bard on a long voyage to her specific destination?&quot;<br>
<br>
were the words that passed Qwik's ears when he walked in ... slowly he walked up and whispered in Casidy's ear &quot;Actually im partial to long , slow walks on the sandy beaches of Oasis&quot; Grinning he walked up to the bar and ordered a round and sat down , easing his body into the chair and sighing in relief from the long walk back to the inn. &quot;If you would something to eat as well&quot; Glancing over towards the table seeing Jzonn,Febereeza and her friend still lost in thought he raised his glass , nodded then turned back to stare at the plate set before him. <p>Qwik Ta`veren Monk of the Wheel and loyal student of Master Chopp Styxx "THE PATTERN WILL SERVE MY WILL!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/12/01 6:17:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Febreeza watched the exchange between Qwik and young Casidy with a raised eyebrow, before sending Casidy a huge grin and a wink.<br>
<br>
I have heard of this place Thurgadin that you mention.  Tales were starting to abound in the Solusek mines I have just come from.  My people are the ones who discovered this new land.  <br>
<br>
They tell stories of fierce cats and strange beasts as have never been seen before, and Giants taller than the trees.  They say there is a lost race of dwarfs, whose skin is snow white.  These I have heard are the ones who live in this Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
But they also say that the land is harsh and cold, and the journey long and perilous.  I have been told, to get there, you have to board a boat that leaves from the new dock that appeared (*whispers* as if by magic) on the water in the North Desert of Ro.<br>
<br>
In fact that is the direction I was headed before I stopped here last night.  I would gladly offer my sword and arm to your service milady.  If I can help in anyway I would be happy to.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/12/01 8:33:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> At Qwiks rapid advance, and soft whispers, a crimson flush flashed on Casidy's cheeks.<br>
<br>
Febreeza had offered her sword to the cause, and Qwik might be pursuaded to travel along as well.... now the question remained would this tracker come along?<br>
<br>
His presence would be invaluable, as Casidy was unsure how to reach the new lands. Febreeza had confirmed the instructions the messanger had given her so things seemed to be proceeding well.<br>
<br>
"What say you Jzonn?" Casidy smiled a slight twinkle in her eye, "Will you lead us forward and onward to this cold new land?"<br>
<br>
